> Get ready for dinner in a flash! This Mediterranean-inspired, plant-based meal is full of flavor, simple to make, and will be on your table in 15 minutes or less. You'll shallow-fry falafel—spiced chickpea croquettes—to a crispy finish and serve over a bed of spinach with juicy tomatoes, briny feta, fresh dill, and earthy red pepper hummus. Finish with a drizzle of garlicky white sauce and sprinkle with almonds for extra flavor and crunch. Fluffy, garlicky pita completes this speedy, savory meal.

Drop @Garlic Herb Butter{2%tablespoon} (in packet) into a #glass{} of warm water to soften. Wash and dry produce.

Thinly slice @Mini Cucumber{1}. Chop @Dill{¼%ounce}(fronds chopped).

In a #bowl{}, mix @Sour Cream{1.5%tablespoon} and @Greek Vinaigrette{1.5%ounce}.

Drizzle @Cooking Oil{1%teaspoon} in a hot #pan{}. Cook @Falafel{10} until golden and crispy, ~{2-3%minutes} per side.

Toast @Whole Wheat Pitas{2}. Spread with garlic herb butter. Cut into wedges.

Toss @Baby Spinach{5%ounce} with creamy dressing.

Top spinach with cucumber, dill, falafel, @Grape Tomatoes{4%ounce}, @Feta Cheese{½%cup}, @Roasted Red Pepper Hummus{4%tablespoon}, and @Sliced Almonds{½%ounce}. Serve with garlicky pita.